LEGAL NOTICE

Date: 12.12.2025

From:
Advocate Rajesh Sharma
For and on behalf of M/s. Rajputana Builders Pvt. Ltd., Udaipur

To,
The Managing Director,
Rajasthan Medical Services Corporation Ltd.,
Swasthya Bhawan, Tilak Marg, Jaipur – 302 015

Sub: Demand Notice for Extension of Time, Release of Withheld Running Bills, and
     Appointment of Arbitrator under Section 11 of the Arbitration & Conciliation Act, 1996
     Re: Construction of 300-Bed Hospital Udaipur — Work Order No. RMSCL/2024-25/Works/4782

Sir,

Under instructions from and on behalf of M/s. Rajputana Builders Pvt. Ltd. (hereinafter "the Contractor"),
we issue this Legal Notice as follows:

1. BACKGROUND
   Work Order No. RMSCL/2024-25/Works/4782 dated 05.05.2024 was issued for construction of 300-Bed Hospital.
   The Contractor commenced work after site handover on 20.05.2024 (45 days late).

2. CONTRACTOR'S PERFORMANCE
   As on 12.12.2025, 41% of sanctioned work has been completed. All work executed is of high quality.

3. DEFAULTS BY EMPLOYER (RMSCL)
   a) Site handover delayed by 45 days — direct loss to Contractor.
   b) Running bills for 7 months unpaid (RA Bills No. 3 to 9 aggregating ₹12.45 Crore).
   c) Approved drawings not supplied for structural steel (Block C) for 4 months.
   d) Variation Order for OPD Block not formally issued despite written demand.

4. DEMAND
   We hereby demand:
   a) Payment of ₹12.45 Crore (withheld running bills) within 15 days.
   b) Formal EOT of 8 months.
   c) Formal Variation Order for OPD Block extra work.

5. CONSEQUENCE OF NON-COMPLIANCE
   If above demands are not met within 15 days, we shall invoke the arbitration clause (Clause 25 of GCC)
   and approach Hon'ble High Court of Rajasthan under Section 11(6) of the Arbitration & Conciliation Act, 1996.

Yours faithfully,

Advocate Rajesh Sharma
On behalf of M/s. Rajputana Builders Pvt. Ltd.
